Non-functional Requirements (NFRs)

1. Performance
   - Image search should take no longer than 2 seconds to return results.

2. Scalability
   - The system should be able to handle large datasets, supporting at least 1 million product images.

3. Accuracy
   - The image matching algorithm should achieve an accuracy of at least 85% on test datasets.

4. Security
   - User-uploaded images must be stored securely and deleted after a session ends.

5. Usability
   - The system should be simple and intuitive for users to upload images and view results.
